- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper discusses the implementation of a computational model using spreadsheets, which falls under the scope of computational engineering. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper involves the development of a conceptual model and formula list, which can be seen as data structures and algorithms for solving the problem. 
- cs.DB (Databases): The paper deals with the organization and manipulation of data in a spreadsheet, which can be considered a type of database. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper may involve the use of AI techniques to optimize the spreadsheet model or to analyze the data. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the implementation of a structured and maintainable spreadsheet model, which can be seen as a software engineering task.
